1
00:00:00,510 --> 00:00:01,770
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,770 --> 00:00:03,480
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,480 --> 00:00:05,140
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:14,490 --> 00:00:15,490
In that case,

5
00:00:16,190 --> 00:00:18,260
could you give me the files
on Temi Bio?

6
00:00:33,770 --> 00:00:35,210
(Episode 18)

7
00:00:36,710 --> 00:00:40,010
I'd like to confirm for myself
whether what you're saying is true.

8
00:00:40,710 --> 00:00:43,980
I have a right to know...

9
00:00:44,250 --> 00:00:48,750
if I was really that clueless
and just fell for the marketing.

10
00:00:51,290 --> 00:00:52,960
Temi Bio...

11
00:00:53,690 --> 00:00:55,630
is in the past.

12
00:00:56,360 --> 00:00:58,600
There's no need
to concern yourself...

13
00:00:59,260 --> 00:01:01,270
with outdated files.

14
00:01:02,230 --> 00:01:05,100
It might not be the past.
It could be our history.

15
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:09,710
Adele Group's bio division started
with Temi Bio.

16
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:12,210
Shouldn't I get my facts straight?

17
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:24,760
Chloe,

18
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:27,660
why are you so obsessed
with Temi Bio?

19
00:01:38,670 --> 00:01:39,900
Here are the lab results.

20
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:47,380
Chloe.

21
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:52,120
She's not really Baek Jin Ju,
is she?

22
00:02:29,950 --> 00:02:34,530
I'm touched that you're so concerned
with Adele Group's history.

23
00:02:35,290 --> 00:02:36,560
I really am,

24
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:41,400
but I can't give you the files
on Temi Bio.

25
00:02:42,070 --> 00:02:43,770
I had them all destroyed.

26
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:48,240
They were a complete waste.

27
00:02:57,520 --> 00:03:00,180
Right. I see, Chairman Park.

28
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:02,090
In that case,

29
00:03:02,190 --> 00:03:04,090
let's just wrap things up for today.

30
00:03:04,090 --> 00:03:05,460
The interview...

31
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:07,990
Okay, everyone,
that's a wrap for today.

32
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:11,300
Thank you for your time, sir.
I know you're very busy.

33
00:03:11,460 --> 00:03:13,770
Chloe, let's go.
Okay, everyone, pack it up.

34
00:03:13,830 --> 00:03:14,970
That's a wrap.

35
00:03:14,970 --> 00:03:16,070
Hold on.

36
00:03:19,140 --> 00:03:21,670
Adele Group's bio division...

37
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:24,840
did not start with Temi Bio.

38
00:03:26,210 --> 00:03:27,250
And that is something...

39
00:03:28,510 --> 00:03:30,780
you would all do well to remember.

40
00:03:38,190 --> 00:03:39,190
I see.

41
00:03:40,090 --> 00:03:41,390
I'll keep that in mind.

42
00:03:52,570 --> 00:03:54,470
I approved this on one condition,

43
00:03:54,470 --> 00:03:56,410
that you'd keep it quiet
and contained,

44
00:03:57,140 --> 00:03:59,380
but you barged into his office
without an appointment.

45
00:04:00,510 --> 00:04:01,780
That was completely out of line.

46
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,410
In Korea... Or rather,

47
00:04:03,980 --> 00:04:07,190
at Adele,
is the chairman's office so sacred?

48
00:04:07,950 --> 00:04:11,390
When I worked overseas,
I met with CEOs all the time,

49
00:04:11,460 --> 00:04:14,260
and walking into their offices
was never an issue.

50
00:04:14,860 --> 00:04:16,730
This isn't overseas.

51
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:21,200
Adele Group has its own rules
and its own culture.

52
00:04:22,130 --> 00:04:23,130
Okay.

53
00:04:23,470 --> 00:04:25,800
It's frustrating,
but I'll try to get used to it.

54
00:04:27,140 --> 00:04:29,970
And there's one thing
I'd like to confirm.

55
00:04:30,740 --> 00:04:33,610
Why are you so interested
in Temi Bio?

56
00:04:34,410 --> 00:04:37,850
Do you have a personal connection
to Temi Bio?

57
00:04:40,180 --> 00:04:43,590
Is being interested in Temi Bio
against the rules...

58
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:45,220
at Adele?

59
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:51,030
The chairman and you
both get so defensive...

60
00:04:51,100 --> 00:04:52,500
whenever Temi Bio is mentioned.

61
00:04:57,740 --> 00:05:02,110
Like the chairman said,
it was an unsuccessful M and A.

62
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:07,010
That's why
it's a sore subject around here.

63
00:05:07,550 --> 00:05:09,950
I expect you to be mindful of that
going forward.

64
00:05:10,010 --> 00:05:13,080
There are so many things
I have to be careful about at Adele.

65
00:05:14,090 --> 00:05:15,290
I'll be on my way.

66
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:24,960
But...

67
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:27,670
do you feel the same way?

68
00:05:29,130 --> 00:05:30,940
Do you really think Temi Bio...

69
00:05:31,770 --> 00:05:33,240
was completely useless?

70
00:05:35,410 --> 00:05:36,410
Yes.

71
00:05:39,710 --> 00:05:43,210
We haven't been able to utilize
any of its technology so far.

72
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:51,920
I hope...

73
00:05:51,990 --> 00:05:54,030
we can work together
to finally make use...

74
00:05:54,230 --> 00:05:56,030
of Temi Bio's technology,

75
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:59,100
so we can change how the chairman...

76
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:00,600
and the world see it.

77
00:06:11,180 --> 00:06:14,610
My life at this company was boring,
but comfortable.

78
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,280
And now? It's a total dopamine rush.

79
00:06:16,810 --> 00:06:20,080
This is a blockbuster movie
in the making, right?

80
00:06:23,650 --> 00:06:24,660
Father.

81
00:06:24,990 --> 00:06:27,590
Has Chloe always been
such a firecracker?

82
00:06:27,860 --> 00:06:31,560
The way she led the film crew
to storm the chairman's office?

83
00:06:32,530 --> 00:06:33,660
That's totally my style.

84
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:37,000
It's the kind of excitement
I've been missing.

85
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,870
That straightforward,
go-getter attitude.

86
00:06:40,540 --> 00:06:42,870
That's just how my Chloe works.

87
00:06:43,210 --> 00:06:45,710
Bold and fearless.
Straight to the point.

88
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:47,950
Taking on challenges directly
is how she became so successful.

89
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:50,680
Some people call her
a natural-born genius.

90
00:06:51,650 --> 00:06:55,190
But no, it's the result
of Chloe working her tail off.

91
00:06:56,650 --> 00:06:59,160
A hardworking genius
who goes for what she wants.

92
00:07:00,290 --> 00:07:03,230
I knew it. She's definitely my type.

93
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:07,100
Father, what do you say
to grabbing a bite...

94
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:10,600
Sorry about that.
What terrible timing.

95
00:07:13,140 --> 00:07:14,410
Now what?

96
00:07:16,710 --> 00:07:18,540
Why? What is it?

97
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:22,750
I seriously don't get
what Ms. Oh is up to.

98
00:07:23,820 --> 00:07:25,250
I'd better go see what she wants.

99
00:07:27,820 --> 00:07:30,050
Father, I'm so sorry
to cut this short.

100
00:07:30,090 --> 00:07:32,790
I'll pull out all the stops
to make it up to you next time.

101
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:35,960
Later.

102
00:07:54,610 --> 00:07:57,520
I guess I'll see you around.

103
00:07:57,580 --> 00:07:59,550
I'm sorry, but can I say something?

104
00:08:00,790 --> 00:08:01,790
No.

105
00:08:02,050 --> 00:08:04,620
You can say two things,
not just one.

106
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:07,530
Then...

107
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:11,930
Please take this as Chloe's agent,
not as her father.

108
00:08:13,730 --> 00:08:15,000
As you may have noticed,

109
00:08:15,170 --> 00:08:17,700
the Adele Group chairman isn't
an easy person to be around.

110
00:08:18,270 --> 00:08:22,510
Please try to make sure
Chloe doesn't cross him.

111
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:25,080
Are you that worried about her?

112
00:08:27,010 --> 00:08:28,880
This is for the good of everyone.

113
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:31,750
Now, if you'll excuse me.

114
00:08:41,890 --> 00:08:44,700
They would've been a great match,
if not for what happened.

115
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:58,840
(Humangen Diagnostic Center)

116
00:09:16,090 --> 00:09:17,860
We should work together...

117
00:09:18,930 --> 00:09:22,100
to fully utilize
Temi Bio's technology?

118
00:09:24,170 --> 00:09:27,040
Will that really help me
get my revenge?

119
00:09:35,150 --> 00:09:37,010
I thought you'd already left.

120
00:09:38,220 --> 00:09:39,250
Choi Yu Na...

121
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:40,920
took...

122
00:09:41,420 --> 00:09:42,650
the DNA test results and...

123
00:09:47,090 --> 00:09:49,190
(Humangen Diagnostic Center)

124
00:09:49,330 --> 00:09:50,900
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

125
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:52,930
James, Chloe's agent,

126
00:09:53,230 --> 00:09:56,170
claimed to be her father,
so I requested a DNA test...

127
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:58,640
and asked to have
the results expedited.

128
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:12,280
(Test Results)

129
00:10:12,350 --> 00:10:13,880
(The test proves
James Lee's paternity of Chloe Lee.)

130
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:18,960
It's confirmed.
Chloe is James's daughter.

131
00:10:19,460 --> 00:10:22,360
This proves that Chloe
can't possibly be Baek Jin Ju.

132
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:34,740
Looks like Choi Yu Na
got the test results.

133
00:10:35,470 --> 00:10:36,940
She must have taken the results...

134
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:40,240
and gone straight
to Chairman Park Tae Ho.

135
00:10:40,580 --> 00:10:41,650
Just...

136
00:10:42,110 --> 00:10:43,450
as we expected.

137
00:10:44,180 --> 00:10:45,380
It's all going according to plan.

138
00:11:33,030 --> 00:11:34,970
We got the samples from...

139
00:11:35,030 --> 00:11:38,040
a father and daughter at our company
who look exactly alike,

140
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:41,970
so the paternity test was bound
to come back positive.

141
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:46,240
They won't suspect
my real identity anymore.

142
00:11:48,610 --> 00:11:49,610
Exactly.

143
00:11:52,650 --> 00:11:53,650
(Humangen Diagnostic Center)

144
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:58,590
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

145
00:11:58,590 --> 00:12:01,230
It was ridiculous to suspect
she was Baek Jin Ju,

146
00:12:01,230 --> 00:12:02,660
who was supposedly dead.

147
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:05,800
It was obvious
even without this test.

148
00:12:06,900 --> 00:12:08,800
They might look a little alike,

149
00:12:09,230 --> 00:12:11,370
but their personalities
and the way they speak...

150
00:12:11,970 --> 00:12:13,300
couldn't be more different.

151
00:12:15,270 --> 00:12:17,740
They're completely different people?

152
00:12:19,340 --> 00:12:20,340
In that case,

153
00:12:20,710 --> 00:12:23,080
could you give me the files
on Temi Bio?

154
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:26,880
Adele Group's bio division started
with Temi Bio.

155
00:12:27,550 --> 00:12:29,550
Shouldn't I get my facts straight?

156
00:12:32,260 --> 00:12:35,290
Are you still not convinced,
even with clear evidence?

157
00:12:35,590 --> 00:12:38,060
You're not going to find
more definitive proof than this.

158
00:12:39,260 --> 00:12:42,800
Regardless of the evidence,
keep an eye on her.

159
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:47,400
Report to me immediately
if she does anything suspicious.

160
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:51,580
Of course.
I'll keep an eye on Chloe,

161
00:12:52,110 --> 00:12:54,610
so you can focus on
speeding up my wedding.

162
00:12:55,780 --> 00:12:57,410
Here we go again with this marriage.

163
00:12:59,250 --> 00:13:01,890
Don't you have any other ambitions?

164
00:13:02,090 --> 00:13:05,020
I need to get married
before I can plan my next move.

165
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:07,930
Unbelievable.

166
00:13:09,390 --> 00:13:11,100
(Adele, 251 dollars)

167
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,200
Oh my.

168
00:13:15,170 --> 00:13:17,300
What the... Unbelievable.

169
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:20,700
What in the world?

170
00:13:21,070 --> 00:13:25,380
What's gotten into you?
You look like you won the lottery.

171
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:30,080
I sure did hit the jackpot.

172
00:13:31,020 --> 00:13:35,090
I heard Adele Group brought in
someone famous from overseas,

173
00:13:35,190 --> 00:13:38,020
and the stock has been hitting
the upper limit every day.

174
00:13:38,820 --> 00:13:42,090
Who cares about the stock price
when I'm about to blow a gasket?

175
00:13:42,890 --> 00:13:44,030
Why's that?

176
00:13:44,330 --> 00:13:45,730
All you care about is money.

177
00:13:45,730 --> 00:13:46,900
Unbelievable.

178
00:13:47,570 --> 00:13:49,630
And to think I vowed
to take you as my husband.

179
00:13:50,330 --> 00:13:53,440
Even after that witch from Adele
ripped my hair out,

180
00:13:53,740 --> 00:13:55,510
I can't say a word...

181
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:58,040
because their stock is soaring
and making them even richer.

182
00:13:58,210 --> 00:14:00,010
Come on, it wasn't that bad.

183
00:14:00,510 --> 00:14:02,310
Just forget about it.

184
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:04,110
Forget it? As if.

185
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:06,020
Just wait until the wedding.

186
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:09,520
I'll put that pipsqueak
in her place first.

187
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:13,790
- Just you wait.
- Honey, come over here.

188
00:14:14,090 --> 00:14:15,530
Leave it!

189
00:14:19,230 --> 00:14:22,830
That tramp Kim Myung Hui
is about to be named president,

190
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,970
and you're telling me
there's no plan to stop her?

191
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,470
She brought in Chloe,

192
00:14:28,070 --> 00:14:29,940
the stock price is soaring
every day,

193
00:14:30,210 --> 00:14:32,780
and she's seamlessly rebranding
the bio division.

194
00:14:33,110 --> 00:14:35,550
We have no grounds to oppose.

195
00:14:35,610 --> 00:14:37,720
If you don't have grounds,
then create them.

196
00:14:37,980 --> 00:14:40,280
If this Chloe person is a problem,
just kick her out.

197
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:47,290
That's what you're all
on my payroll for, isn't it?

198
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:51,330
Seriously, that temper of hers.

199
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,000
Then again,

200
00:14:54,570 --> 00:14:55,570
I guess...

201
00:14:56,570 --> 00:14:58,070
that's also part of her charm.

202
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:01,910
Mr. Song.

203
00:15:02,810 --> 00:15:04,140
She's killing me.

204
00:15:05,140 --> 00:15:07,180
Where's Ms. Oh?
What's this about her...

205
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:10,750
canceling all my credit cards?
What's with the sudden tantrum?

206
00:15:10,850 --> 00:15:14,020
Just go on inside.
You'll see everything's fine.

207
00:15:14,290 --> 00:15:15,290
What?

208
00:15:20,060 --> 00:15:24,700
It's obvious they're in the middle
of plotting something in there.

209
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:27,100
Well...

210
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,030
Mr. Song.

211
00:15:29,670 --> 00:15:31,670
Man, I'm disappointed in you.

212
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:33,800
You're disappointed?

213
00:15:33,870 --> 00:15:37,210
I expect this from Ms. Oh,
but for you to betray me too...

214
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:39,110
Betray you?

215
00:15:39,280 --> 00:15:41,650
I wouldn't dream of it.

216
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:43,310
You totally did.

217
00:15:43,310 --> 00:15:45,350
Otherwise, why would I even be here?

218
00:15:45,980 --> 00:15:49,090
I missed dinner,
I had to cancel my plans,

219
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:50,990
and just wasted my time.

220
00:15:51,060 --> 00:15:53,090
You haven't eaten?

221
00:15:53,820 --> 00:15:55,490
Seriously? How could you...

222
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:57,030
Just go.

223
00:15:57,860 --> 00:16:00,200
It's fine. What about Ms. Oh?

224
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:02,100
I'll just take the heat for you.

225
00:16:02,870 --> 00:16:06,040
For you, that's the least I can do.

226
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:08,110
Okay, I'm out of here.

227
00:16:08,270 --> 00:16:12,440
Right. Hey, make sure
you get something to eat.

228
00:16:14,910 --> 00:16:16,080
Mr. Song!

229
00:16:17,010 --> 00:16:18,420
Where's Hyun Jun?

230
00:16:35,100 --> 00:16:36,700
A business magazine interview?

231
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:38,870
Already acting
like the president, are you?

232
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:42,370
Not a chance. Not while I'm around.

233
00:16:42,670 --> 00:16:44,510
What have you done now?

234
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:48,580
If you're that curious,
why don't you go ask the chairman?

235
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:01,790
You're putting my appointment
as president on hold?

236
00:17:03,190 --> 00:17:05,500
The board of directors
raised some concerns.

237
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,200
They're not convinced...

238
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:10,300
someone with only
a background in jewelry...

239
00:17:11,870 --> 00:17:13,540
should run the bio division.

240
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:16,610
That's why I brought in Chloe
to help me.

241
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:20,280
You promised me the position
if I brought her on board.

242
00:17:21,210 --> 00:17:24,920
I'm not trying to break my promise.
I just want to be sure.

243
00:17:26,020 --> 00:17:28,890
We still don't know if Chloe
will be a blessing or a curse.

244
00:17:29,550 --> 00:17:32,220
If she turns out to be a blessing,
the presidency is yours.

245
00:17:32,490 --> 00:17:33,520
But if she's a curse,

246
00:17:34,930 --> 00:17:36,730
then that changes things.

247
00:17:37,330 --> 00:17:39,400
I assure you,
Chloe will be an asset.

248
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:41,430
She's an expert with a proven...

249
00:17:41,430 --> 00:17:43,130
Forget world-renowned.

250
00:17:44,070 --> 00:17:46,900
I'm going to test her my way.

251
00:17:48,370 --> 00:17:49,370
Test her?

252
00:17:50,670 --> 00:17:51,680
Here.

253
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:53,040
(Bio Division:
New Symbol Evaluation Plan)

254
00:17:53,610 --> 00:17:55,380
You know about...

255
00:17:55,380 --> 00:17:57,950
next week's evaluation
for the new symbol, don't you?

256
00:17:59,020 --> 00:18:00,020
Yes.

257
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:03,950
We've developed
Options A and B internally,

258
00:18:04,620 --> 00:18:08,330
and shareholders will decide
through a blind vote.

259
00:18:08,430 --> 00:18:09,490
As for Option C,

260
00:18:10,730 --> 00:18:12,000
have Chloe submit her own design.

261
00:18:12,460 --> 00:18:14,970
One week isn't nearly enough time
to prepare.

262
00:18:15,030 --> 00:18:18,500
If she can deliver results
under these adverse conditions,

263
00:18:20,170 --> 00:18:22,640
I'll acknowledge Chloe's talent.

264
00:18:23,810 --> 00:18:27,010
And I'll make you president
for bringing her on board,

265
00:18:28,310 --> 00:18:31,220
regardless of what the board says.

266
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:39,920
If Director Kim Myung Hui
becomes president,

267
00:18:41,230 --> 00:18:43,690
will she be helpful to our plan?

268
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:47,400
Is that what's been on your mind?

269
00:18:49,870 --> 00:18:53,140
To find out why Chairman Park Tae Ho
went after Temi Bio,

270
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:55,640
and what he wanted,

271
00:18:57,510 --> 00:18:59,610
I endured the humiliation...

272
00:19:02,180 --> 00:19:04,850
of seeing my father disgraced.

273
00:19:07,850 --> 00:19:11,720
In the end, Chairman Park Tae Ho
killed my father just to ensure...

274
00:19:12,390 --> 00:19:13,990
the success of the Adele Group.

275
00:19:15,790 --> 00:19:18,500
If I make Choi Yu Na
get in the way of that success,

276
00:19:20,460 --> 00:19:22,270
he'll get rid of her too.

277
00:19:23,330 --> 00:19:26,400
We can't let Director Kim Myung Hui
become president.

278
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:31,410
We need to destroy the Adele Group,
and she'll just try to protect it.

279
00:19:32,110 --> 00:19:36,110
But she's the only one
who appreciates Temi Bio's value.

280
00:19:37,450 --> 00:19:39,280
If Director Kim becomes president...

281
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:42,850
and brings the technology
my dad left behind to light,

282
00:19:44,220 --> 00:19:48,530
wouldn't that, in a way,
restore his honor?

283
00:19:50,290 --> 00:19:51,430
I'm tempted.

284
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,800
If you feel tempted,
pay close attention.

285
00:19:55,430 --> 00:19:58,300
You can never really know
what's in someone's heart.

286
00:20:00,100 --> 00:20:04,110
Director Kim might not be the person
we think she is at all.

287
00:20:05,910 --> 00:20:07,710
Whether she helps us
or becomes a problem,

288
00:20:08,180 --> 00:20:09,710
watch her closely...

289
00:20:10,680 --> 00:20:11,780
from a safe distance.

290
00:20:13,020 --> 00:20:14,790
A safe distance.

291
00:20:16,150 --> 00:20:18,090
Close enough to use her
when she's helpful,

292
00:20:18,890 --> 00:20:21,990
but far enough to drop her
without hesitation when she's not.

293
00:20:24,860 --> 00:20:26,300
That's what you mean, right?

294
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:54,090
Chloe isn't Baek Jin Ju.

295
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:00,260
(DNA Parentage Test Report)

296
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:05,900
(The test proves
James Lee's paternity of Chloe Lee.)

297
00:21:09,210 --> 00:21:10,210
Hold on.

298
00:21:11,110 --> 00:21:12,580
You ran a paternity test?

299
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:16,910
To see if Chloe's really
James's daughter? No way.

300
00:21:17,110 --> 00:21:20,080
It was to confirm
she isn't Baek Jin Ju.

301
00:21:23,420 --> 00:21:24,890
Stop being so ridiculous.

302
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:28,990
Dead people don't just
come back to life.

303
00:21:30,330 --> 00:21:32,360
Stop chasing a ghost
and snap out of it.

304
00:21:35,100 --> 00:21:37,000
You should be focusing
on our wedding.

305
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:44,980
Even if Chloe isn't Jin Ju,

306
00:21:44,980 --> 00:21:47,280
and we go through with this wedding,

307
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:51,380
nothing will change between us.

308
00:21:56,790 --> 00:21:57,790
Park Min Jun!

309
00:22:03,790 --> 00:22:05,360
So it's confirmed.

310
00:22:07,230 --> 00:22:10,470
Chloe really is Chloe.

311
00:22:34,790 --> 00:22:35,790
A ghost?

312
00:22:37,090 --> 00:22:38,900
I'm not chasing a ghost.

313
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:40,660
I was hoping you'd come back,

314
00:22:40,730 --> 00:22:42,770
even if it was in this capacity.

315
00:22:44,670 --> 00:22:46,170
That's what I wanted to believe.

316
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:49,970
Even if it was a false hope...

317
00:22:50,910 --> 00:22:52,380
that was bound
to be shattered like this.

318
00:23:35,190 --> 00:23:36,290
Today,

319
00:23:39,090 --> 00:23:40,290
I lied...

320
00:23:41,590 --> 00:23:42,760
perfectly.

321
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:49,500
Wearing the shoes you gave me,

322
00:23:50,430 --> 00:23:51,940
I became
an even more perfect version...

323
00:23:53,870 --> 00:23:55,240
of Chloe.

324
00:23:59,910 --> 00:24:00,940
And now,

325
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:04,480
you must be convinced
that Chloe isn't Baek Jin Ju.

326
00:24:10,650 --> 00:24:11,660
As for me,

327
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:16,930
do I feel happy
about becoming Chloe,

328
00:24:22,230 --> 00:24:23,600
or sad?

329
00:25:30,230 --> 00:25:32,200
(Request for Proposal
and Statement of Work)

330
00:25:35,670 --> 00:25:38,640
Aren't we set for
the symbol evaluation next week?

331
00:25:38,940 --> 00:25:42,850
The chairman wants you
to design and submit a symbol.

332
00:25:44,310 --> 00:25:47,080
You want me to come up with a design
with only one week left?

333
00:25:48,550 --> 00:25:52,290
So basically, he wants me
to give up, fail, or be humiliated.

334
00:25:53,460 --> 00:25:57,160
I guess the chairman isn't happy
about me being at Adele.

335
00:25:58,660 --> 00:26:01,100
Think of it as a test.

336
00:26:02,630 --> 00:26:05,600
Is he trying to test
what I'm capable of?

337
00:26:05,970 --> 00:26:08,100
He's testing my decision
to bring you in.

338
00:26:08,410 --> 00:26:09,640
And if I refuse?

339
00:26:10,270 --> 00:26:12,280
Then I won't get to head
the bio division,

340
00:26:12,580 --> 00:26:15,480
and we'll lose our chance
to utilize Temi Bio's technology.

341
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:19,980
I know it's a lot to ask,

342
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:22,550
but I hope you don't give up.

343
00:26:23,350 --> 00:26:24,850
When I was in the jewelry business,

344
00:26:24,850 --> 00:26:26,390
I was constantly tested...

345
00:26:27,090 --> 00:26:28,490
and had to prove myself.

346
00:26:28,590 --> 00:26:29,890
That's how...

347
00:26:30,530 --> 00:26:32,800
I made a name for myself
and earned my place at Adele.

348
00:26:36,300 --> 00:26:37,770
But this time, I can't do it alone.

349
00:26:38,570 --> 00:26:41,810
If you give up,
I'll have no way to prove myself.

350
00:26:44,310 --> 00:26:46,140
(Bio Division:
New Symbol Evaluation Plan)

351
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:55,520
These files are no use to me.

352
00:26:56,790 --> 00:26:59,990
I need to see all the files
on the rebranding first.

353
00:27:02,290 --> 00:27:03,290
Does that mean...

354
00:27:04,830 --> 00:27:07,600
Being evaluated, tested,
and having to prove myself.

355
00:27:08,330 --> 00:27:10,230
So what you're saying is,
they want a fight.

356
00:27:11,300 --> 00:27:13,970
I've never backed down
from a fight like this.

357
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:16,770
And I've never lost one, either.

358
00:27:18,110 --> 00:27:20,110
I'll get the files you need
right away.

359
00:27:24,310 --> 00:27:25,720
(Jewelry Division,
Director Kim Myung Hui)

360
00:27:35,330 --> 00:27:36,330
Here you go.

361
00:27:38,030 --> 00:27:39,730
Don't you think this is better?

362
00:27:39,900 --> 00:27:41,360
Why don't you take a look at this?

363
00:27:43,370 --> 00:27:44,670
But this is a little...

364
00:27:48,100 --> 00:27:50,910
This one's for Director Kim,
and this one's for you.

365
00:27:52,940 --> 00:27:54,740
Don't even think about
switching them.

366
00:27:55,710 --> 00:27:57,210
Relax, I won't.

367
00:27:58,010 --> 00:28:01,450
She's been working so hard
she hardly eats and has no appetite,

368
00:28:01,790 --> 00:28:03,920
but your food is the only thing
she'll even touch.

369
00:28:04,290 --> 00:28:06,860
If I could,
I'd give her my lunch too.

370
00:28:11,760 --> 00:28:13,000
Hi there!

371
00:28:17,500 --> 00:28:20,340
Who's he bringing all that food to?

372
00:28:21,170 --> 00:28:24,370
Beats me.
He's never been the thoughtful type.

373
00:28:31,450 --> 00:28:33,520
(Consultant, Chloe Lee)

374
00:28:35,350 --> 00:28:37,750
So this is why
everyone raves about Chloe.

375
00:28:38,690 --> 00:28:41,930
You even make the heart
of the person next to you race.

376
00:28:43,190 --> 00:28:46,360
My pride is on the line.
Of course I'm on edge.

377
00:28:47,100 --> 00:28:49,700
Of course. The work. The nerves.

378
00:28:50,530 --> 00:28:53,040
That's not what I meant
about my heart racing but...

379
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,210
If there's anything
I can do to help,

380
00:28:57,110 --> 00:28:58,110
just say the word.

381
00:29:14,060 --> 00:29:17,660
Dead people don't just
come back to life.

382
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:20,730
Stop chasing a ghost
and snap out of it.

383
00:29:42,820 --> 00:29:43,820
Forget it.

384
00:29:44,750 --> 00:29:46,860
The symbol evaluation
is today, right?

385
00:29:47,420 --> 00:29:48,420
That's right.

386
00:29:53,300 --> 00:29:55,370
I trust everything is ready
for the evaluation?

387
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:59,240
The outcome is a given,
so what's the point of preparing?

388
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:02,970
Just go with the evaluation results.

389
00:30:03,040 --> 00:30:06,110
Don't go soft on that witch,
you hear me?

390
00:30:08,510 --> 00:30:09,810
I feel the same way.

391
00:30:10,680 --> 00:30:13,980
I hope you will handle this fairly,
based on today's evaluation.

392
00:30:21,490 --> 00:30:22,730
(Consultant, Chloe Lee)

393
00:30:26,730 --> 00:30:28,330
Don't get your hopes up.

394
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:33,100
The higher your hopes,

395
00:30:35,170 --> 00:30:36,610
the greater the disappointment.

396
00:30:40,610 --> 00:30:41,610
We'll see about that.

397
00:30:42,410 --> 00:30:45,720
We'll find out soon enough
who's going to be disappointed.

398
00:30:48,180 --> 00:30:49,190
Ms. Choi.

399
00:30:51,090 --> 00:30:54,390
The voting for the new symbol design
has started.

400
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:02,930
(BIT Logo Design Contest Voting:
Option A, Option B, Option C)

401
00:31:03,030 --> 00:31:04,600
(Jewelry Division,
Director Kim Myung Hui)

402
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:08,470
What's the status?

403
00:31:08,770 --> 00:31:10,270
The voting is about to close.

404
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:12,780
(BIT Logo Design Contest Voting:
Option A, Option B, Option C)

405
00:31:12,840 --> 00:31:14,610
(Voting closed)

406
00:31:14,980 --> 00:31:16,010
Voting is closed.

407
00:31:32,330 --> 00:31:34,560
(Jewelry Division,
Director Kim Myung Hui)

408
00:32:07,100 --> 00:32:10,100
(Pearl in Red)

409
00:32:10,300 --> 00:32:11,370
Why are you avoiding me?

410
00:32:11,370 --> 00:32:14,840
Have you lost interest because
I'm not who you were hoping for?

411
00:32:14,900 --> 00:32:17,170
Don't try so hard
to get Min Jun's attention.

412
00:32:17,170 --> 00:32:18,210
Aren't I a better catch?

413
00:32:18,270 --> 00:32:20,110
He's still just a mistress's son.

414
00:32:20,110 --> 00:32:21,580
A mistress as a group president?

415
00:32:21,680 --> 00:32:24,880
You dare try to take my son's place
and run the group?

416
00:32:24,950 --> 00:32:27,180
If you're that bitter,
take it up with the chairman.

417
00:32:27,180 --> 00:32:28,320
You shameless tramp.

418
00:32:28,320 --> 00:32:31,450
I'll never lose to you,
no matter what you try to pull.

419
00:32:31,450 --> 00:32:33,160
Mark my words. Whatever you get,

420
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:34,820
I'll take it all from you.

421
00:32:36,660 --> 00:32:38,660
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
